Kudlow ya ce na gaba na coronavirus stimulus lissafin zai haɗa da ƙarin dubawa, ƙara haɓaka akan fitarwa
Mai ba da shawara kan tattalin arziki na White House Larry Kudlow ya yi alkawari a ranar Lahadi cewa gwamnatin tarayya za ta mika ragamar aiki a kan fitar da kaya da kuma fitar da wani zagaye na dubawa a matsayin wani ɓangare na kunshin ƙwayoyin cuta na coronavirus na gaba.
Jawabin Kudlow na zuwa ne bayan mako guda inda fadar White House ta yi fatan yanke harajin da majalisa ta harbe shi.
“Akwai rajistan $1,200 da ke zuwa. Wato zai zama wani ɓangare na sabon kunshin. Na fi son a yanke haraji, a saman wannan rajistan,” in ji Kudlow a kan “Jihar Tarayyar.”
“Amma, zama cewa kamar yadda ya iya, a siyasance, ba ya aiki.”
Duk da yake ba a sanar da yarjejeniyar ba a hukumance, Sakataren Baitulmalin Steve Mnuchin da shugaban ma'aikata na White House Mark Meadows sun kasance a Capitol Hill kwanan nan don tattauna cikakken bayani game da sabon kunshin taimako tare da shugabannin majalisa.
A kan kawo karshen karin dala 600 na rashin aikin yi da gwamnatin tarayya ke samarwa, Kudlow ya yi ikrarin cewa karin kudi yana cutar da kananan sana'o'i daga hayar ma'aikata.
“Mun samu ambaliyar bincike da kiran waya da korafe-korafen cewa kananan shaguna da kasuwanni, gidajen cin abinci ba za su iya hayar mutane baya ba,” inji shi.
