“The Persians” Review: Aeschylus na Tsohon Hoton Aeschylus
Babu wani aiki mai yawa, har ma da makirci, a cikin “Farisa.”
Mutane kawai suna yin magana game da su, suna magana (a hankali) game da abubuwan da suka faru (admittedly na mummunan irin) wanda ya faru da nisa.
Amma duk da haka wannan gidan wasan kwaikwayo na kasar Girka ya ba da sauti da fushin gale-karfi.
A ganinsa, wasan kwaikwayo ya yi kama da busa ga plexus na hasken rana, dauke numfashinka - tasiri ne kawai dan kadan ta hanyar kallon kan layi.
An fara samarwa a 472 B.C., Aeschylus “The Persians” an dauke shi mafi tsufa a wasan Girkanci.
Wannan Dimitris Lignadis ya watsa shirye-shirye a ranar Asabar daga tsohuwar amphitheater na Epidaurus; a cikin ruhun gidan wasan kwaikwayo, babu rikodi a kan layi.
An samo asali ne a matsayin wani ɓangare na aselepeion na birnin (cibiyar warkarwa) saboda Helenawa sunyi la'akari da ma'auni tsakanin jiki da ruhu mai muhimmanci ga lafiyar lafiya.
Bari mu yi tunanin wannan falsafar.
Wasan kwaikwayon ya yi hulɗa da bayan Salamis, yakin ruwa wanda Helenawa suka ƙaddamar da sojojin Persian 2,500 shekaru da suka wuce.
A lokacin da sararin samaniyarmu ke rufewa, shi ne downright vertigo-inducing zuwa kusan shiga cikin masu sauraro masu rai a kallon (subtitled) 'yan wasan kwaikwayo masu rai duk hanya a Girka yayin da suke yin wasan kwaikwayo na millenniums.
Aeschylus kansa ya yi yaƙi a Salamis, amma wasa yana da karkatar: Wannan tsohon soja na gefen nasara ya kafa labarinsa a tsakanin ci, yana jefa ido mai ban tausayi a kan abokan gaba na kwanan nan” baƙin ciki.
Wani jigon maza na Persian, sanye da siket mai launin tanti-launin fata da fararen button-ƙasa, ya buɗe aikace-aikacen.
Suna cikin babban birninsu suna jiran labarai na sarkin su, Xerxes, wanda ya kashe shi tare da Athens.
Shigar da mahaifiyar Xerxes, Sarauniya Atosa (Lydia Koniordou), a cikin wani babban gown mai launin fata wanda ya nuna yana sa mata, maimakon baya; ta kasance mutum a cikin wani nau'i na masana'anta, mai rauni da kuma m.
